00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:50.000
and it did make

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:51.000
my presentation harder

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:52.000
to remember,

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:53.000
but I've received a lot

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:54.000
of great feedback about them,

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:55.000
and I'm just really hammering home

00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:57.000
that the simpler you can make them,

00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:58.000
the more the audience

00:17:58.000 --> 00:17:59.000
is going to remember them.

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.000
I do, you know,

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:02.000
little things

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.000
that I didn't bring up,

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.000
these particular slides

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:06.000
take into account color blindness.

00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:07.000
That's a nice thing

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:08.000
to do as well,

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:09.000
but supportive and simple

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:11.000
is really the message there.

00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:12.000
Thank you as well.

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:14.000
Great, and last question.

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:16.000
Do you make any supplementary docs

00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:17.000
for your presentations

00:18:17.000 --> 00:18:18.000
since you're not designing

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:20.000
the slides to be self-explanatory?

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:21.000
How do you handle requests

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:22.000
for slides?

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:23.000
Absolutely.

00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:26.000
If I'm sending my slides

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:27.000
to someone,

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.000
I would definitely send

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:29.000
supplementary information

00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:30.000
if it's something

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:31.000
really content-heavy.

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:32.000
You know,

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:33.000
things that you refer to

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:34.000
in your presentation,

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:35.000
you can then make notes,

00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:36.000
see supplementary table,

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:37.000
that's a really good tactic

00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:38.000
for doing this sort of thing.

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:39.000
I agree with that, yes.

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:40.000
Great.

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:41.000
Thank you, Farida.

00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:42.000
Thank you very much.

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:44.000
Thank you.

